<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40109b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40109b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40109b"> 109(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Aeshma </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: In the hierarchy of Zoroastrian demons (<i>daevas</i>), Aeshma is opposed to Asha Vahishta, the Amesha Spenta that is the hypostasis of &ldquo;Truth.&rdquo; This opposition also reflects Aeshma&apos;s position as messenger of <i>Angra Mainyu</i> (Yasht 19.46), for in the hierarchy of divinities, Asha is the messenger of Spenta Mainyu, the instrument through which Ahura Mazda&apos;s realized (&ldquo;created by His thought&rdquo;) creation. </mm> </dd></dl>
